dct_title_s: Eastern Turkey in Asia. Deir ez Zor, sheet 44. Series G.S.G.S. no. 1522
dct_description_sm: "Drawn and printed at the War Office, March 1915." Relief shown by form lines and by spot heights. Includes an index to adjoining sheets, and a glossary. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. no. 1522. Relief shown by form lines and spot heights. Some sheets from this set were revised and issued by War Office. Geographical Section. General Staff, published as G.S.G.S. no. 1522, 1522a. Series covers Mesopotamia and eastern Anatolian parts of Ottoman Empire. "Compiled for the Geographical Section, General Staff, War Office, by Lieut. Col. F.R. Maunsell, C.M.G. [from] Chesney's Euphrates Expedition, 1837, Report on Navigation of Euphrates from Birijik to Feluja, by Mr. H.R. Dobbs, Indian Political Dept. Feb. 1903, Archaological Reise in Euphrat und Tigris by Saare & Herzfeld 1908-10, 'Vom Mittelmeere zum Persischen Golf' by Max Freiherr von Oppenheim, 1893, Kiepert's Karte von Kleinasien - Sheet Nisibin 1914." With Glossary. Set complete, see index.
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain. War Office. Intelligence Division
